entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is your dream job

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: dream job i think to consult about mental health and how to how to intervene effectively with different cultures and doing research and consulting work and getting to travel basically that those would be the main characteristics

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay do you consider yourself more shy or outgoing

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think that is a false dichotomy but i do consider myself shy but at the same time outgoing in the sense that i push myself to do things outside of my comfort zone and i am determined to do what it takes to become successful

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that makes sense sometimes when i am feeling tense i turn on the fish tank screensaver hey i know it is not hawaii but it is the best i have got what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i listen to music and just lay on my bed and i guess you could say do mindfulness and really just take my mind off of things

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: also breathing exercises which i am learning more about as well as exercise

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: cool how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty good i do not get angry a lot so as far as angry temperament i am pretty good at that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h what month is this may probably two months ago and i argued via text message so it is not really intense arguing but i guess you could call it arguing in a sense over whether or not i should be forgiven for something that i thought was minor with a friend i have had for a few years

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i felt anxious sad and angry yeah those are the main emotions

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how do you know them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i know them because i think i am pretty in touch with my emotions and being able to identify them and then i will notice the physical manifestations of emotions like if i if my heart is racing or if i am getting sweaty if i am if my breathing is more shallow i will know i am anxious i will know something is bothering me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h that i wish i had handled differently i guess related to this argent i went out one night and got a little too intoxicated and ended up calling a person for a ride home but that really upset that person and i know that it was not such a big deal but i wish i had not have let myself get to that point it it impacted a relationship and i also felt really bad about what i did

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: hardest decision wow probably deciding what type of graduate program to go into i briefly went to law school and decided not to do that so afterwards well after dropping out i had to really rethink what it is that i wanted to do and what i wanted to dedicate my life to go into debt for spend a lot of energy on

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: one person is my mentor who i met in two thousand five and she is a judge and i met her when i was in counity college and she really opened my eyes to possibilities and made me feel that i would be able to achieve certain things

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty easy well it is easy for me to sleep what is not easy is getting up

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because usually i do not forward look forward to what i have to do that day and the thought of it is you know just makes me wanna stay in bed also i wake up pretty tired not really feeling refreshed

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think just self talk about how what i have to do is not that bad or that the things that i am doing now are gonna end pretty soon with the end of the school year trying to think of things that i can look forward to in the week also listening to music and browsing the internet kinda gets my mind going

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: feeling wow feeling emotionally drained on some ways and at the same time feeling like i have accomplished a lot and that i have grown so a mix of ambivalence and feeling drained and a mixture of feeling accomplished and proud at the same time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: in two thousand six

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the convergence of a lot of stressful factors i was out of touch with my mom i started well i had transferred to a university that was pretty rigorous and just all those changes going on really exacerbated things that were already there depressive tendencies that were already there and it got to a point where i just felt really overwhelmed

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: this past weekend i reconnected with some old friends and it was really good to see them and be back in touch again

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: awesome how would your best friend describe you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: people have different takes on on me i do not have one best friend but i think people would describe me as very analytical sensitive intelligent intellectual

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h what are some things you wish you could change about yourself

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i wish that i did not or wait i wish i was better able to cope with my anxiety and depression which i am working on and i wish that i had more energy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what advice would you give to yourself ten or twenty years ago

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: start going to therapy now but yeah i really would and also to what how old am i twenty eight ten years ago eighteen okay so graduating from high school i would tell myself to pick up some more job skills so that i would not have to struggle as much in the future and to seek out mentors to get a clearer idea of what i wanted to do as a career

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are you most proud of in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think the fact that i am in grad school and coming from the background that i that i come from low socio economic status and just pushing through challenges to get here
